  "texts": [
    "As we show with several cases of lexical gaps, language modeling bias is closely related to a second key concept, linguistic diversity, which refers to linguistic constructs and ultimately ideas that are difficult to translate into certain languages.",
    "We argue that if we are to do justice to the more profound dimensions of diversity expressed in different languages and prevent epistemic injustice by means of language modeling bias, we need to pay attention to precisely these constructs and the cultural particularities they reveal.",
    "In our second contribution, we detail how the causes of language modeling bias are in part a consequence of the flawed methods by which language technology is currently developed.",
    "In doing so, we refer primarily to the academic apparatus of knowledge and technology production, but also outline how this apparatus is intertwined with the private sector and its interests.",
    "To support our claim, we analyze how many databases and language processing systems that are purportedly multilingual have been developed from the perspective of a single language (English)."
  ],
